In the future we might very likely need distance fields ANYWAY
to increase the range of zoom for example
or constant-stroke-width that doesn't scale with updated scale of the shape!
(width is inpedendent from bounds/matrix).

Benefits:

- quick changes like strokes, color, effects
- better quality for higher zoom
- simpler logic with cache textures, only existing in JS basically(except when bigger padding is needed)
- if we modify color of many objects at once, then this solution will be way faster. Modyfing points always happens for one/two paths at once, no more
- Split the process of obtainign data from curves from applying an effect

Downsides:

- when bound box(or to be more precise padding) will increase we will have a problem, and then it's not only JS thing to rerender texture, we have to ask for it form zig
- Drawing while editing points might be slower(firstly draw to texture, then texture to canvas)
- Quality _MIGHT_ be worst, like we have with our rotate icon

What we would need from a distance field texture:

- signed distance
- angle where the closest point is
- t parameter - or actually we might need t like distance!

